## What I Learned

Building Receipt Memory taught me:
- Conversational interfaces for financial data require balancing helpfulness with precision
- Source attribution is critical for user trust in AI-generated answers
- Natural language queries are more intuitive than traditional filters/search
- Receipt metadata (carbon footprint, warranties) becomes valuable when easily queryable

## Future Enhancements

- Voice queries ("Hey Siri, ask Receipt Memory...")
- Predictive insights ("You usually spend $X on groceries, you're 20% over this month")
- Shared receipts for households ("What did my partner buy at Target?")
- Receipt recommendations ("You bought batteries 6 months ago, they might need replacing")

## Built With

- Python (backend logic)
- HTML/CSS/JavaScript (demo interface)
- JSON (data storage)
- Claude API (planned for production)

